Hey, you're now within your mind. you're free to speak and feel. You are who you are here. But to provide yourself with some direction, let's talk about your observations of their livelihood and your views of their life and how/what you want and expect from your journey. I predominantly want to live in the city because I need people. Why? I actually don't like a lot of types of people. And I really have the choice to avoid these people. I feel like in the process of meeting so many people, you sort of forget how to speak for yourself and how you feel truly and deeply. You can never be your full self with those people because there is a chance of them of leaving. I feel like the issue is you somewhat in a very deep level are looking for validation from people. you want to be liked, in the office or outside office to some extent. And you're scared that if they don't like you and you don't like them, the world will fall apart. In the process of that, you mask what you really want to say and feel at some points. I remember that in the past, I didn't think twice who I was speaking to, I just was so open. and the people who like you and you like will attract eventually.  Remember that your connection with other people should not define how you feel. Their reaction to what you say should not define how you feel. I am permanent and I KNOW who I AM. That is all and all that matters

column5: Just remember, everything around you is a simulation in life. Without social media and whatsapp and instagram, I would never know whats happening in someone else's life. EVER. Without reels and shorts, I would end up for sure FILLING MY TIME in with other things - whether youtube videos, friends, somethign to learn. WITHOUT YOUTUBE AND NETFLIX AND SHOWS - I would be replacing that very time with something else. I would have to. Like there is no other way. Who you meet infront of you is an interaction opportunity that you may either discount or hype based on their instagram, whatsapp, or whatever else. In actuality, every interaction should be considered without knowing anything else about them but who they are in front of you.
